    "recap_headline": "Mississippi State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BILOXI -\nThird-ranked Mississippi State erupted for seven runs in the seventh inning to rally past Tulane 11\u20137 Tuesday night in front of the second-largest crowd in Keesler Federal Park history.\nA crowd of 6,112 watched the Diamond Dawgs erase a five-run deficit and turn a quiet night at the plate into a late offensive explosion as MSU improved to 15-2 on the season.\nTulane jumped in front early, scoring twice in the first inning on an RBI single by Jason Wachs and a sacrifice fly from Nolan Nawrocki. Mississippi State answered immediately when\nNoah Sullivan\ndoubled home\nDrew Wyers\nbefore\nReed Stallman\nfollowed with an RBI single to tie the game at 2\u20132 in the bottom of the inning.\nThe Green Wave regained control in the fourth when Nate Johnson blasted a two-run homer to right field, pushing Tulane ahead 4\u20132. Tulane added three more runs in the seventh, highlighted by RBI hits from Tye Wood and Matthias Haas and a steal of home by Haas, stretching the lead to 7\u20132.\nThat's when the Bulldogs' offense came alive.\nState loaded the bases in the bottom of the seventh before\nAce Reese\ndelivered the biggest swing of the night, launching a grand slam to left-center field to suddenly pull the Bulldogs even.\nThe inning was far from finished.\nSullivan reached on an error and later scored on Stallman's RBI single.\nGehrig Frei\nfollowed with a run-scoring double, and\nChone James\nadded an RBI single to cap a stunning seven-run outburst that gave Mississippi State a 9\u20137 lead.\nThe Diamond Dawgs padded the lead in the eighth when Wyers lifted a sacrifice fly and Frei drove in another run with a single, extending the advantage to 11\u20137.\nMississippi State pounded out 12 hits in the victory. Frei finished with two hits and two RBIs, Stallman added two hits and two RBIs, and Reese's grand slam accounted for four RBIs.\nOn the mound,\nDane Burns\npicked up the win in relief as the MSU bullpen stabilized after Tulane's seventh-inning surge.\nChris Billingsley Jr.\nand\nBen Davis\ncombined to close the final two innings without allowing a run.\nTulane collected 10 hits in the loss, including three from Wachs and a pair from Wood.\nThe Bulldogs begin Southeastern Conference play at Arkansas this weekend. Game 1 is slated for Friday at 6 p.m. on SEC Network +.\nVisit\nwww.HailState.com\nfor the latest news and information on the baseball program. Fans can also follow the program on social media by searching 'HailStateBB' on\nX\n,\nFacebook\nand\nInstagram\n."
  },
